Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.56,0:02:13.56,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:133566,133566}However, the only thing that stayed on Maya's mind after she got off stage was her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:28.10,Episode title,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:140724,148106}{\an5\pos(766,720)\fscy95\blur1\fad(800,0)}—Episode 16—\NTrace of Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.51,0:02:27.51,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:147514,147514}Dear mother.\NHow are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.34,0:02:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:148348,148348}Today is the last day\Nof "The Smile of Stone."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:154921,154921}What are you doing, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.19,0:02:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:157190,157190}We only have an hour\Nuntil the play starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.79,0:02:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:159793,159793}You know you will be fined\Nif you are late, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.32,0:02:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:162328,162328}Oh, you can take all your time\Ntomorrow to write that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:166332,166332}It's not like your mom\Nwill go away. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:170737,170737}Maya, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.37,0:02:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:171371,171371}Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.77,0:02:59.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:179779,179779}I'm sorry, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.08,0:03:02.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:182082,182082}It's been two years, but I haven't even written a single letter to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.91,0:03:05.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:185919,185919}You don't even know that Tsukikage Theater went out of business, nor that I moved into an apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:10.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:190857,190857}You don't even know that I am on stage either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.02,0:03:16.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:196029,196029}Today's the last day of our play.\NI wish you had a chance to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.63,0:03:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:203636,203636}Mother…?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:26.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:206506,206506}No, that's not…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:215448,215448}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:218885,218885}Mom…\NThat's my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:220887,220887}Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.75,0:03:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:222756,222756}Please let me off here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:225458,225458}Please let me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.46,0:03:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:227460,227460}What's going on with you, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.19,0:03:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:229195,229195}My mother.\NThat was my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.30,0:03:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:237303,237303}She was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.87,0:04:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:242876,242876}Maya, are you sure\Nyou weren't dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:250116,250116}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:255655,255655}Mother, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:267967,267967}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:270236,270236}You'll be late for the play, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:273106,273106}Our play…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.64,0:04:34.64,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:274641,274641}The Smile of Stone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.40,0:04:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:275408,275408}Hey, did you see our audience today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.77,0:04:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:277777,277777}Orion Theater's actors are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.54,0:04:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279546,279546}That's right. Their last day\Non "Hamlet" was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.74,0:04:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:282749,282749}Miss Tsukikage is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:286653,286653}Okay, guys.\NLet's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289856,289856}Hmm, where's Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.77,0:05:03.77,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:303770,303770}Manpuku Ken
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.17,0:05:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305171,305171}Where's Haru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:307073,307073}That's what I want to ask you, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:310543,310543}I thought she went to visit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.01,0:05:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313013,313013}She disappeared on her way to a rest home, and we haven't heard from her since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:317484,317484}Rest home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:319519,319519}Then, her lungs were bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:322389,322389}Yes. For a long time,\Nshe was just lying in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.92,0:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:324924,324924}We wanted to let you know,\Nbut we didn't know where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:328261,328261}So, we had to make a—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:331131,331131}Maya, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:331865,331865}Hello? Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:333466,333466}Thanks.\NI'll have to call you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.93,0:05:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:336936,336936}So, you have to at least\Ntell us your address—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:340073,340073}Hey, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.67,0:05:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:342676,342676}Oh, she's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.31,0:05:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:344310,344310}Maya has been doing\Na great job all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:347480,347480}Of course. She has to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350917,350917}The success of this play\Nis up to her acting as a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.56,0:06:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361561,361561}I'll be watching\Nyour acting today, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.36,0:06:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:364364,364364}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.16,0:06:07.16,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:367167,367167}"The Smile of Stone's"\Nlast day has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.83,0:06:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:371838,371838}The join play by Tsukikage and Ikkakuju Theater went on in an old cafe converted into an underground theater with full audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.41,0:06:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382415,382415}That's Kitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384718,384718}Now, I would like to announce a qualified contributor who will take care of the doll Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393960,393960}A contributor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.39,0:06:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395395,395395}Yes, the person must honestly love and care about Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:42.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:402302,402302}She's been missing…\NThen that must have been my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.30,0:06:47.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:407307,407307}Tuberculosis.\NThat's why she was so thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.71,0:06:55.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:415715,415715}I'm sorry, so sorry, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.55,0:06:58.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418551,418551}For not being able to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.58,0:07:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:422589,422589}So, Ms. Isabella, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.29,0:07:09.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:429295,429295}I'm the only one\Nshe has… the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.93,0:07:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:432932,432932}Hey…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433366,433366}Look at that…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.36,0:07:15.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:435368,435368}Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:23.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:443009,443009}The mask is gone,\Nthe mask of a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452452,452452}Shoot, the important doll\Nis all soaking wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:455422,455422}Hanna, please help me\Nchange Elizabeth's outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.02,0:07:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463029,463029}Frederica, when did you start\Nplaying with your dolls as a hobby?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.73,0:07:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:466733,466733}Oh, Mr. Gallison,\Nwhat's with you and your duster?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.20,0:07:51.20,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:471204,471204}The water covering\NMaya hid her tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.44,0:07:55.44,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:475442,475442}The play went on as if nothing happened,\Nand it was saved by Rei's wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.65,0:08:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490657,490657}What was it?\NWhat was that mysterious attraction?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493360,493360}Yeah, I was sucked into some kind of… passion, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497297,497297}They were all skilled actors.\NEspecially the doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501935,501935}Maybe she's a good find.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.74,0:08:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:508742,508742}What are you doing,\Ntaking your mask off on the stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.54,0:08:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:514547,514547}Because of your unprofessional behavior, this important last day of the play was almost jeopardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.12,0:08:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:521121,521121}Miss Tsukikage, Maya saw someone that seemed like her mother on the way to the theater today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527427,527427}It doesn't matter what it is, it still doesn't give you a reason to take your mask off on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.39,0:08:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531398,531398}Maya… you failed as an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:08:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:535201,535201}Failed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:08:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:536903,536903}You won't be in the next play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:08:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:539072,539072}You're on probation for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.74,0:09:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:543743,543743}Probation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:545645,545645}I knew I had to kill myself\Nbefore I went onto that stage…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:550650,550650}You couldn't help it, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.31,0:09:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:552318,552318}What we wear is a glass mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.28,0:09:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:555288,555288}Glass mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.65,0:09:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:557657,557657}Yes.\NA fragile glass mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:560627,560627}That's why it's so easy to break it\Nand reveal the real face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.43,0:09:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:564431,564431}You can tell an actor's\Nability to keep the mask on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:37.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:577644,577644}A glass mask…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.38,0:09:46.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:586386,586386}I took the mask off on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.12,0:09:49.12,Retrospective,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589122,589122}If you fail, "The Crimsson Goddess"\Nwill go to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.09,0:09:53.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593093,593093}No, it's over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:54.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594828,594828}Miss Tsukikage must have given up on me.\NI won't be able to play "The Crimson Goddess" anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:09:58.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598865,598865}Then, for what reason did I throw my mother out of my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.73,0:10:01.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:601735,601735}Mother… Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.18,0:10:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617183,617183}Maya, can you stop the alarm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.88,0:10:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:620887,620887}Hey, Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:626092,626092}Oh, where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:45.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:645412,645412}Mother… I want to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:48.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:648148,648148}I want to put my face in your chest\Nand be your daughter again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.99,0:10:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659993,659993}These are the candidates\Nfor Helen Keller.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.92,0:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:662929,662929}There are about 15 candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.93,0:11:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:666933,666933}Thanks for all your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.83,0:11:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:669836,669836}This one is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.13,0:11:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:672138,672138}Hmm, an exception?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674274,674274}Yes. I haven't seen her\Nmovement or speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.77,0:11:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:678778,678778}She played as a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.44,0:11:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:681448,681448}But I saw great talent in that role\Nwithout any movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:687087,687087}Okay, we'll have her\Nas a candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:691458,691458}Haseagawa…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:692258,692258}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.89,0:11:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:694894,694894}How did you become\Nsuch a great scout?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:697497,697497}Uhh…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:698131,698131}Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.41,0:11:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:711411,711411}I wonder where the hell Maya is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.18,0:11:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:714180,714180}Oh, that's Maya.
Comment: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:05.72,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:725725,725725}Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:09.47,0:12:09.47,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:729478,729478}#Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:12.39,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:732397,732397}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:12.39,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:732399,732399}It has been three days since Maya started walking, looking all over for her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.60,0:12:20.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:740607,740607}She might not be in Tōkyō anymore.\NBut where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:25.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:745478,745478}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.61,0:12:28.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748615,748615}"The Cherry Tree\Nof Dream Festivals."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.55,0:12:30.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:750550,750550}That's the play where Himekawa Ayumi\Nplays a daughter of a wealthy family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.25,0:12:37.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757257,757257}Ayumi is looking fabulous on stage,\Nand look at me: I'm on probation and looking terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.06,0:12:42.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762062,762062}I wonder if the day that I can become an actress will ever come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.83,0:12:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770837,770837}Thank you so much for your visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.20,0:12:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:774207,774207}The actors were really excited to see you visit them, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777677,777677}I heard Himekawa Ayumi is doing great.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.64,0:13:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:780647,780647}She was born to play the main role.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:783883,783883}I'm looking forward to her future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.75,0:13:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:785752,785752}Mr. Ota! Kawamura Yoshiko\Nfell off the stairs and broke her leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.09,0:13:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:790090,790090}What?\NThen make her walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:792726,792726}There's no one else for her part.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795028,795028}But it's all swollen\Nand she can't even move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.79,0:13:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:799799,799799}Damn. Then we'll have\Nto change the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:803136,803136}Call Mr. Isomura, the playwright.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.47,0:13:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:805472,805472}No, there's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:811244,811244}Mr. Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.05,0:13:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:820053,820053}Is this your shelter\Nfrom the rain, little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:823390,823390}You…\NLeave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:827227,827227}I can't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.42,0:13:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828428,828428}You are our important substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:831164,831164}A substitute?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.70,0:13:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:833700,833700}Mr. Ota, could you tell her\Nwhat the play is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.93,0:13:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:837937,837937}But, we only have another hour before our play starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.10,0:14:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841107,841107}It's impossible for her\Nto get the words memorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.04,0:14:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:843043,843043}It's okay.\NHere, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:845311,845311}Wait a minute.\NI haven't said that I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:849349,849349}You will do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.81,0:14:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:852819,852819}Or are you going to give up the chance of getting on such big stage so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860760,860760}Besides, this is a play that's been talked about a lot. Your only fan might be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:867567,867567}Mr. Purple Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.46,0:14:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869469,869469}Here, get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.40,0:14:33.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873406,873406}I will never like this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:880947,880947}Go on ahead and memorize the words.\NWe don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:884918,884918}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.72,0:14:53.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893727,893727}Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.62,0:14:55.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:895628,895628}Kitajima Maya!\NWhy is she here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.86,0:14:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:897864,897864}Everyone, let me introduce Kitajima Maya.\NShe'll play as a substitute for Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.33,0:15:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:906339,906339}Ayumi, she will play\Nas your cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.20,0:15:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:909209,909209}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:911344,911344}Cousin?\NI'll be her cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915148,915148}Yes. Under a very different circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.25,0:15:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919252,919252}This is our first play together.\NLet's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.93,0:15:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:932932,932932}Sorry we couldn't find you a better place,\Nbut we're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.56,0:15:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:936569,936569}Your appearances are in the third and fourth scenes of the first act, and the fifth in the second act.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.77,0:15:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:940774,940774}It starts at 6 PM.\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.01,0:15:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:948014,948014}I only have 45 more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.49,0:16:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:963496,963496}So that's the girl\NMiss Harada called "stage storm."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.26,0:16:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:967267,967267}I heard she tied with Himekawa Ayumi\Nin the amateur contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.73,0:16:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:970737,970737}But, so what?\NIt's impossible in such a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:973540,973540}It's not like she only has\Nto remember her part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.98,0:16:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983983,983983}What's wrong with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:985752,985752}Can't she hear the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988088,988088}Look at her concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.36,0:16:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002369,1002369}It's bad luck for us.\NShe'll be on stage when we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.90,0:16:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1005905,1005905}"Stage storm…"\NShe might overwhelm us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1010076,1010076}We finally got our part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.97,0:16:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1011978,1011978}I hope she forgets her words\Nand falls silent or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.01,0:16:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1015015,1015015}I know…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.34,0:16:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1015348,1015348}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.51,0:16:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1017517,1017517}I have a good idea, Bungo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020120,1020120}T-That's a little too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.68,0:17:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022689,1022689}Hmph. It's eat or be eaten\Nin this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.69,0:17:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1031698,1031698}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1033366,1033366}Why don't you change and do your makeup now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1037203,1037203}But I have only gotten\Nto the third scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1039839,1039839}You can read even after\Nthe play has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1045745,1045745}Well, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047647,1047647}Here, hurry.\NI can help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.01,0:17:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051017,1051017}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:36.79,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1056790,1056790}The script Bungo switched was the original one before Isomura, the playwright, did the editing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.09,0:17:42.09,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1062095,1062095}Isomura drastically changed the fourth scene, not only the words, but also the storyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:49.60,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1069602,1069602}The time is during the Meiji Era,\Nwhen Rokumeikan was flourishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:53.17,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1073173,1073173}This is a drama about\NKaizōji, a baron, and his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:17:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076643,1076643}Uncle, Aunt.\NLook at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:17:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1079512,1079512}Ms. Barnette, my tutor, taught me\Nhow to greet in the Western way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.15,0:18:05.15,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1085151,1085151}Ayumi's role is as a baron's\Nproud granddaughter, Tsukiyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:09.15,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1089155,1089155}Maya's role is a daughter born to his fifth son, Yukihiro.\NAs a geisha, she grew up with discrimination.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.99,0:18:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1096996,1096996}I finally got through\Nwith the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.23,0:18:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1099232,1099232}The rest is how to play\NChie my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1101935,1101935}What a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.07,0:18:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104070,1104070}She has memorized\Nall of the words already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.47,0:18:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106473,1106473}Well, too bad; your words\Nwill be useless on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:31.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1111845,1111845}Mr. Purple Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.68,0:18:33.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1113680,1113680}Please watch me tonight\Nif you are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:36.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1116016,1116016}You can see my Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1123890,1123890}You weren't back at the promised time,\Nso I came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.69,0:18:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1127694,1127694}I put her in as a substitute,\Nso I'll be held responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.63,0:18:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1131631,1131631}I knew you would say that, so I went ahead\Nand canceled your appointments.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.73,0:18:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135735,1135735}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.47,0:18:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138471,1138471}How did it go between\NTsukiyo and Mr. Funakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141875,1141875}It went fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.44,0:19:04.44,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1144444,1144444}The third scene of the first act went smoothly,\Nbut the fourth was about to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148548,1148548}It's my go at it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.81,0:19:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1150817,1150817}Yukihiro, my father,\Nwill come back soon, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1153653,1153653}Bad news about Mr. Yukihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.12,0:19:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1156122,1156122}What about Yukihiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.69,0:19:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159693,1159693}He went off to be an entertainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.12,0:19:22.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162128,1162128}Different! This is different\Nfrom what I've read!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1168902,1168902}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.57,0:19:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1173573,1173573}This is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1174908,1174908}The father was supposed to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.04,0:19:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1178044,1178044}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1180814,1180814}Oh, this is the old script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.88,0:19:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184884,1184884}Uncle Yukihiro\Nbecame an entertainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.62,0:19:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1187620,1187620}How embarrassing.\NI wonder if Chie knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.59,0:19:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1190590,1190590}Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.82,0:19:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191825,1191825}How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.65,0:19:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192659,1192659}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1194361,1194361}Chie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.72,0:19:55.72,Thought,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1195729,1195729}They're calling me.\NI have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.93,0:19:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1199933,1199933}Little girl, no, you can't.\NDon't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.77,0:20:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1204771,1204771}No!\NThe play is on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210877,1210877}She came out.\NWhat nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.01,0:20:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1215015,1215015}Chie, your father is an\Nembarrassment to our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.41,0:20:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218418,1218418}And Chie, you are, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220553,1220553}Why don't you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.45,0:20:22.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1222455,1222455}Say something, but what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.92,0:20:25.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1225925,1225925}Chie is supposed to have a long speech about her sad and miserable life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:30.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1230430,1230430}I wonder what she will do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.70,0:20:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241708,1241708}Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.53,0:21:05.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1265532,1265532}What a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.83,0:21:06.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266833,1266833}Not only doesn't she have to say anything now…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:10.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270837,1270837}…but by biting on the lily,\Nshe expresses her sorrow and bitterness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:22.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1282282,1282282}What should I do?\NHow should I react to this Chie?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.65,0:21:25.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1285652,1285652}I can't get the play going…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.68,0:21:27.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1287687,1287687}How stupid are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:29.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1289222,1289222}Falling into the very trap\Nthey have created.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294461,1294461}Ayumi, it's not your turn yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.49,0:21:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1299499,1299499}Mr. Utahiko, Ms. Kyoko,\Nyour mother is calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.30,0:21:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304304,1304304}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.00,0:21:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1305005,1305005}Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.47,0:21:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307474,1307474}She made those two get off the stage…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.54,0:21:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1310543,1310543}Where is this play going?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.95,0:21:59.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1319953,1319953}Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:03.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1323590,1323590}Kitajima Maya…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.02,0:22:06.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326026,1326026}I never thought our battle would be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.30,0:22:19.30,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1339305,1339305}Maya, who came out on the stage not even knowing the storyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.87,0:22:25.87,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1345879,1345879}Ayumi, who came out on the stage when it wasn't even her turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.15,0:22:30.15,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1350150,1350150}The two stared at one another with their spirits challenging each other on the tense stage.
